<TITLE> Padma Bridge construction starts in fiscal 2008-09: adviser </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 15 (bdnews24.com)  Construction of the much-talked-about Padma Bridge will start in fiscal 2008-09, communications adviser MA Matin said Sunday. At a meeting with an Asian Development Bank delegation led by country director Hua Du, the adviser said Padma Bridge is an important project. "Construction of the bridge should start soon in the interest of people," the government said in a statement. Matin said Bangladesh received offers of an estimated $1,200 million in credit assistance for the project. The ADB pledged $350 million, the World Bank $300 million and Japan Bank for International Cooperation $350 million. DFID and the Netherlands promised $200 million in combined funds. Hua Du reiterated her assurance to help the project. bd
